cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SD, cs.CL

This paper deals with the use of social media and bots to manipulate public opinion, which falls under the category of social informatics (cs.SI). The study also involves machine learning and cognitive behavioral modeling techniques, which could be classified under cybernetics (cs.CY) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The large dataset analysis and characterization of users could also be relevant to statistical analysis and machine learning (cs.SD) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
